  "title": "Safety Officer #79900",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Construction</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Safety Officer</strong></li><li>Working Location: Jurong/Island Wide</li><li>Working Hours: 5.5 days (Mon - Fri 8.00am - 6.00pm; Sat 8.00am - 12.00pm)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic salary up to $6,000 + Variable Bonus</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent Role</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Make sure all work follows the WSH Act, relevant regulations, and company safety rules.</li><li>Carry out regular site safety checks and audits.</li><li>Keep safety records up to date (risk assessments, method statements, safe work</li><li>procedures, permits, incident/near-miss reports, toolbox meeting notes, induction logs).</li><li>Check that workers use PPE, follow safe work procedures and keep good housekeeping.</li><li>Work with site supervisors, subcontractors, clients, and main contractors on safety,</li><li>progress, quality, and compliance matters.</li><li>Give brief progress updates to the main contractor/client when needed</li><li>Check workmanship quality, especially for ceiling and partition works: alignment,</li><li>finishes, installation details, and compliance with drawings/specifications.</li><li>Support incident and accident investigations. Suggest and put in place preventive actions.</li><li>Run or arrange safety inductions, toolbox talks, safety briefings, and in-house training.</li><li>Keep the site ready for inspections at all times.</li><li>Keep the site clean and orderly and store materials and tools safely.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>3 years of relevant experience</li><li>Registered Workplace Safety & Health Officer with MOM</li><li>Must possess personal vehicle or Class 3 driving license</li><li>Willing to travel around Singapore from site to site</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#79900 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Angel Lim | EA Reg No.: R1769781</p>",
